HTS ML VALIDATION

This document shows validation summaries for the HTS Machine Learning Screening Application developed for Machakos, Nairobi, Siaya, Homabay counties.

Positive Precision by County for Different Risk Factor Combinations

Predictions are not binary “positive” or “negative”; rather, they are numbers between 0 to 1 akin to probabilities. For each threshold from 0 to 1, we calculate precision and recall and plot the points on a curve and thus come up with cut off points.

In HTS Model, there are 4 Risk Outcomes; Low Risk, Medium Risk, High Risk, Highest Risk. Different cut-off marks are defined for the risk outcomes by different counties. Across models - the threshold is set based on precision, which is different for every county.

For Siaya County: we expect that of the people we test with a “Highest Risk Outcome” 75.2% will be positive
